Setup NAT Gateway:


### 2.1 Create a static Public IP (outbound IP)

```bash
az network public-ip create \
  --resource-group agicdemo \
  --name aks-nat-pip \
  --sku Standard \
  --allocation-method Static
```

Verify:

```bash
az network public-ip show \
  -g agicdemo \
  -n aks-nat-pip \
  --query ipAddress \
  -o tsv
```

Save this IP — it will be your **final outbound IP**.

---

### 2.2 Create the NAT Gateway (THIS is missing)

```bash
az network nat gateway create \
  --resource-group agicdemo \
  --name aks-nat-gateway \
  --public-ip-addresses aks-nat-pip \
  --idle-timeout 10
```

Verify immediately:

```bash
az network nat gateway show \
  -g agicdemo \
  -n aks-nat-gateway \
  --query id \
  -o tsv
```

You **must** see an ID like:

```
/subscriptions/.../resourceGroups/agicdemo/providers/Microsoft.Network/natGateways/aks-nat-gateway
```

